<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;626.1 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Scope and purpose of the Job Training Partnership Act. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
It is the purpose of the Job Training Partnership Act (JTPA or the Act) to establish programs to prepare youth and adults
facing serious barriers to employment for participation in the labor force by providing job training and other services
that will result in increased employment and earnings, increased educational and occupational skills, and decreased
welfare dependency, thereby improving the quality of the work force and enhancing the productivity and competitiveness
of the Nation (section 2). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;626.2 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Format of the Job Training Partnership Act regulations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Regulations promulgated by the Department of Labor to implement the provisions of the Act are set forth in parts
626 through 638 of title 20, chapter V, of the Code of Federal Regulations, with the exception of the veterans' employment
program's chapter IX regulations of the Office of the Assistant Secretary for Veterans' Employment and Training,
which are set forth at part 1005 of title 20. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Nondiscrimination and equal opportunity requirements and procedures, including complaint processing and
compliance reviews, will be governed by the provisions of 29 CFR part 34 and will be administered by the Department
of Labor (Department or DOL) Directorate of Civil Rights. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) General authority for the JTPA regulations is found at section 169 of the Act. Specific statutory authorities
other than section 169 are noted throughout the JTPA regulations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;626.3 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Purpose, scope, and applicability of the Job Training Partnership Act regulations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Parts 626 through 638 of this chapter and part 1005 of chapter IX (Veterans' employment programs under title IV,
part C of the Job Training Partnership Act) establish the Federal programmatic and administrative requirements
for JTPA grants awarded by the Department of Labor to eligible grant recipients. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Parts 626 through 638 of this chapter and part 1005 of chapter IX apply to recipients and subrecipients of JTPA funds.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

