<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart H_[Reserved] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Subpart I_Disaster Relief Employment Assistance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;631.80 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Scope and purpose. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 This subpart establishes a Disaster Relief Employment Assistance program under title IV, part J of JTPA which shall
be administered in conjunction with the title III National Reserve Grants Programs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;631.81 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Availability of funds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Funds appropriated to carry out this subpart may be made available by grant to the Governor of any State within which
is located an area that has suffered an emergency or a major disaster as defined in paragraphs (1) and (2), respectively,
of section 102 of the Disaster Relief Act of 1974 (42 U.S.C. 5122(1) and (2)) (referred to in this subpart as the ``disaster
area''). The Secretary shall prescribe procedures for applying for funds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;631.82 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Substate allocation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (a) Not less than 80 percent of the grant funds available to any Governor under &sect;631.81 of this part shall be allocated
by the Governor to units of general local government located, in whole or in part, within such disaster areas. The remainder
of such funds may be reserved by the Governor for use, in concert with State agencies, in cleanup, rescue, repair, renovation,
and rebuilding activities associated with such major disaster. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The JTPA title III program substate grantee for the disaster area shall be the designated local entity for administration
of the grant funds under this subpart. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;631.83 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Coordination. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Funds made available under this subpart to Governors and units of general local government shall be expended in consultation
with_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Agencies administering programs for disaster relief provided under the Disaster Relief Act of 1974; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (b) The JTPA title II administrative entity and the private industry council in each service delivery area within
which disaster employment programs will be conducted under this subpart. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;631.84 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Allowable projects. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Funds made available under this subpart to any unit of general local government in a disaster area_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Shall be used exclusively to provide employment on projects that provide food, clothing, shelter and other humanitarian
assistance for disaster victims; and on projects involving demolition, cleanup, repair, renovation, and reconstruction
of damaged and destroyed structures, facilities, and lands located within the disaster area; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) May be expended through public and private non-profit agencies and organizations engaged in such projects. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;631.85 Participant eligibility. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 An individual shall be eligible for disaster employment under this subpart if such individual is_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a)(1) Eligible to participate or enroll, or is a participant or enrolled, under Title III of the Act, other than an
individual who is actively engaged in a training program; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (2) Eligible to participate in programs or activities assisted under Native American and Migrant Programs; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (3) Unemployed as a consequence of the disaster. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) [Reserved].
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;631.86 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Limitations on disaster relief employment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 No individual shall be employed under this subpart for more than 6 months for work related to recovery from a single
natural disaster (described in &sect;631.3(f) of this part). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;631.87 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Definitions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

