<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
In addition to the definitions contained in sections 4, 301, 303(e), and in &sect;626.4 of this chapter, the following
definitions apply to the administration of Title V of the Act and this part: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Absent parent
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means an individual who is continuously absent from the household and who is a non-custodial parent of a dependent
child receiving aid to families with dependent children (AFDC) under part A of title IV of the Social Security Act (42
U.S.C. 601, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
et seq.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Disability assistance
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means benefits offered pursuant to Title XVI of the Social Security Act, relating to the supplemental security income
program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Federal contribution
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the amount of the Federal component of cash payments to individuals within the participating State under welfare
and/or disability assistance programs, including Part A of Title IV of the Social Security Act. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart B_Program Planning and Operation 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.200 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Allotments to States. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) For each program year for which funds are appropriated to carry out programs under this part, the Secretary shall
pay to each participating State the amount the State is eligible to receive in accordance with this part. No payments
shall be made for any years for which funds are not appropriated and/or not available (section 502(a)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) If the appropriation is not sufficient to pay to each State the amount it is eligible to receive in accordance with
this part, the State shall receive a percentage of the total available funds equal to the percentage of its bonus compared
to the national total of bonuses (section 502(b)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) If an additional amount is made available after the application of paragraph (b) of this section, such additional
amount shall be allocated among the States by increasing payment in the same manner as was used to reduce payment, except
that no State shall be paid an amount which exceeds the amount to which it is eligible (section 502(c)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.205 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Notice of intent to participate. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Any State seeking to participate in the incentive bonus program shall notify the Secretary of its intent to do so
no later than 30 days before the beginning of its first program year of participation (i.e., June 1) (section 505(a)).

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Pursuant to instructions issued by the Secretary, the notification referenced in paragraph (a) of this section
shall be in the form of a letter from the Governor to the Secretary advising the Secretary of the State's intention to
apply for, receive and expend bonuses under this program in a manner consistent with this part (section 505(b)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) After the State's submission of a notice of intent to participate, incentive bonuses may be claimed by a State for
any individual who: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1)(i) Was an absent parent of any child receiving AFDC at the time such individual was determined to be eligible for
participation in programs under the Act; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Has participated in education, training, or other activities (including the Job Corps) funded under the Act;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Pays child support for a child specified in paragraph (c)(1) of this section following termination from activities
funded under the Act; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2)(i) Is blind or disabled; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Was receiving disability assistance at the time such individual was determined to be eligible for participation
in programs under the Act; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Has participated in education, training, or other activities (including the Job Corps) funded under the Act;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Earns from employment a wage or an income (section 506). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) A Governor may withdraw the State's participation in the incentive bonus program in any program year by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
submitting a written notice of withdrawal.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
