<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.210 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Incentive bonus program applications. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Any State seeking to receive an incentive bonus under this title shall submit an Incentive Bonus Program application
pursuant to instructions issued by the Secretary that will contain the criteria for approval of such application.
Each application shall contain, at a minimum, the following information: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A list of eligible individuals who met the requirements of &sect;637.220 of this part during the program year;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The amount of the incentive bonus attributable to each eligible individual who is claimed by the State; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) A statement certifying the availability of documentation to verify the eligibility of participants and the amount
of the incentive bonus claimed by the State (section 505(b)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The application for any program year shall be submitted by the State to the Secretary no later than 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
August 31 following the end of the program year for which the bonus is being claimed. A copy of such application shall
also be submitted at the same time to the appropriate DOL Employment and Training Administration Regional Office.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.215 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Review and approval of applications for incentive bonus payments. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Secretary shall review all applications for overall compliance with JTPA, the requirements of this part,
and the instructions issued by the Secretary. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Secretary shall inform a State within 30 days after receipt of the application whether or not its application
has been approved. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) If the application is not approved, the Department shall issue an initial notice of denial of payment indicating
the reasons for such denial. The Governor will then have 30 days to respond to the reasons for the denial before a final
decision is made. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) If the Department determines that the additional information provided does not adequately respond to the questions
raised in the initial review process, a final denial of payment shall be issued. The Governor may then appeal the decision
in accordance with the procedures at subpart H of part 627 of this chapter (sections 504(c) and 505(c)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.220 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Eligibility criteria for individuals to be counted in determining incentive bonuses. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
An individual shall be eligible to be counted as part of the State's request for an incentive bonus payment under this
part if the individual: (a)(1) Was an absent parent of any child receiving AFDC at the time such individual was determined
to be eligible for participation in programs under the Act; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Has participated in education, training, or other activities (including the Job Corps) funded under the Act;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Pays child support for a child specified in paragraph (a)(1) of this section following termination from activities
funded under the Act; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b)(1) Is blind or disabled; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Was receiving disability assistance at the time such individual was determined to be eligible for participation
in programs under the Act; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Has participated in education, training, or other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
activities (including the Job Corps) funded under the Act; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Earns a wage or an income from employment (section 506). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.225 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Determination of incentive bonus. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The amount of the incentive bonus to be paid to each State shall be the total of the incentive bonuses claimed for each
eligible individual within the State. The amount of the incentive bonus to be paid each State shall be determined by
the sum of: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
