<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) An amount equal to the total of the amounts of child support paid by each individual who is eligible under &sect;637.220(a)
of this part, for up to 2 years after such individual's termination from JTPA; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) An amount equal to the total reduction in the Federal contribution to the amounts received under title XVI of the
Social Security Act (42 U.S.C. 1381, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
et seq.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) by each individual who is eligible under &sect;637.220(b) of this part, for up to 2 years after such individual's
termination from JTPA (section 503). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.230 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Use of incentive bonuses. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) During any program year, the Governor may use an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
amount not to exceed 5 percent of the State's total bonus payment for the administrative costs incurred under this
program, including data and information collection and compilation, recordkeeping, or the preparation of applications
for incentive bonuses (section 504(a)(1)(A)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The remainder, not less than 95 percent of the incentive bonuses received, shall be distributed to SDAs and Job
Corps Centers within the State in a manner consistent with an agreement between the Governor and these SDA's and centers.
This agreement shall reflect an equitable method of distribution which is based on the degree to which the effort of
the SDA and/or Center contributed to the State's qualification for incentive bonus funds under title V (section 504(a)(1)(B)).

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Not more than 10 percent of the incentive bonus received in any program year by each SDA and/or Job Corps Center may
be used for the administrative costs of establishing and maintaining systems necessary for operation of programs
under title V, including the costs of providing incentive payments described in paragraph (d) of this section, technical
assistance, data and information collection and compilation, management information systems, post-program followup
activities, and research and evaluation activities (section 504(a)(2)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Each SDA and/or Job Corps Center may make incentive payments to service providers, including participating State
and local agencies, and community-based organizations, that demonstrate effectiveness in delivering employment
and training services to eligible individuals under this title (section 504(b)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) All remaining funds received by each SDA shall be used for activities described in sections 204 and 264 of JTPA and
shall be subject to the regulations governing the operation of programs under titles II&hyph;A and II&hyph;C of JTPA.
All remaining funds received by each Job Corps Center shall be used for activities authorized under part B of title
IV (section 504(a)(2). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart C_Additional Title V Administrative Standards 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and Procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.300 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Management systems, reporting and recordkeeping. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Governor shall ensure that the State's financial management system and recordkeeping system comply with

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subpart D of part 627 of this chapter. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Notwithstanding the provisions of &sect;629.455 of this chapter, the Governor shall report to the Secretary
pursuant 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to instructions issued by the Secretary regarding activities funded under this part. Reports shall be required semi-annually
and annually. Reports shall be provided to the Secretary within 45 calendar days after the end of the report period.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The Governor shall assure that appropriate and adequate records are maintained for the required time period to
support all incentive bonus payment applications. Such records shall include documentation to support individuals'
eligibility under this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.305 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Federal monitoring and oversight. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Secretary shall conduct oversight of the programs and activities conducted in accordance with this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;637.310 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Audits. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Governor shall ensure that the State complies with the audit provisions at &sect;629.480 of this chapter. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

